result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamael J Coley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Heroin(>3-10g), a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(d)2.
  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>15-40g), a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)3.

Defendant Jamael J Coley in court with attorney Michael John Steinle.  Laura A. Crivello appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 
Court addresses the correspondence, date stamped and to remain sealed in the court file. 
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Brenda C. 
  



AS TO COUNT 1: 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS, concurrent with COUNT 2, with credit for 1 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 4 YEARS.  

AS TO COUNT 2: 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 11 YEARS, concurrent with COUNT 1, with credit for 1 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 4 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 7 YEARS.  

Defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program ONLY after serving 2 YEARS and 0 MONTHS of initial confinement in each COUNT 1 and 2. 
Defendant IS NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

AS TO COUNT 1 AND 2: 
Provide DNA sample (unless previously submitted) and pay surcharge; 
Court costs, fines, assessments, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b). If not paid in full by release date it will convert into a civil judgment. 

Conditions of Extended Supervision as to COUNT 1 and 2 are as follows:
- Maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant NOT possess or
  use any controlled substances unless by valid prescription. 
- AODA assessment and comply with any treatment, including drug
   and alcohol testing. 
- No firearms, weapons   
- Obtain/maintain full time employment;
- No use or possession of illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia.

Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession; Voting.
